        "timestamp": "2020-04-16 15:18:21.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1\n\nIn looking at CADI Filter, I see you have added a null Check.  \n\nFor performance reasons, the design is to always return a Valid Object.  You can use org.onap.aaf.cadi.taf.NullTafResp, if you cannot think of a valid way to return a Response.",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "132f3bac98b73ef60736ec2f6736bb768cee4c99",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 3289,
          "name": "Jonathan Gathman",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jgonap@stl.gathman.org",
          "username": "instrumental"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-04-16 15:24:37.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review+1\n\nOn more careful notice, the Null Check is only in Exception, thus is not part of the normal performing loop.  I will look a bit more more",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
      {
        "id": "e18ea68d9629b261cae0f0e78cb33ece64ca9627",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 3289,
          "name": "Jonathan Gathman",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "jgonap@stl.gathman.org",
          "username": "instrumental"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-04-16 15:33:39.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nThe biggest operational change I see is the change of the default of needing \"/locate/\" to indicate desire for Default Locator, versus lack of \"/locate/\" allows for use of (exiting, but improved SingleLocator\".  There may need to be some testing to validate it works with all the existing Automated Services within ONAP, however, it is a reasonable change, consistent with the intent of \"SingleLocator\".",
        "patchset_number": 3
      },
